I believe the issue is in this code from fetch.ts:

```
    // correct for archive node sending one block too many
    console.log(`Found ${fetchedActions.length} actions: ${fetchedActions.map(x => x.actionState.actionStateOne)}`)
    if (fetchedActions.length !== 0 &&
        fetchedActions[0].actionState.actionStateOne ===
        actionStates.fromActionState) {
        fetchedActions = fetchedActions.slice(1);
```

Should be 

```
    // correct for archive node sending one block too many
    console.log(`Found ${fetchedActions.length} actions: ${fetchedActions.map(x => x.actionState.actionStateOne)}`)
    if (fetchedActions.length !== 0 &&
        fetchedActions[1].actionState.actionStateOne ===
        actionStates.fromActionState) {
        fetchedActions = fetchedActions.slice(1);
```

